event.title: fire on an army patrol in the Bekaa Valley during a weekend

data.event: Family feud leaves two people dead in Palestinian camp . MIEH MIEH/BEIRUT: Rival Palestinian families clashed in a southern refugee camp on Saturday and armed groups opened fire on an army patrol in the Bekaa Valley during a weekend marked by a series of security incidents.

Two Palestinians were killed and three were wounded early Saturday morning as Palestinian fighters from rival families battled in the Mieh Mieh refugee camp outside of the southern coastal city of Saida.
